the werewolves might expect you to protect them and kill someone else. In general, you should avoid revealing your identity unless absolutely necessary.\n\n\n\n\nYou are Heather, your role in this game is guard.\nWerewolf game starting. Initializing day-night cycle.\nSYSTEM: Starting day-night cycle for Day 1\nSYSTEM: Night 1 begins. Werewolves and special roles take actions.\nGuard action processed. Roberta is protected this night.\nGuard has chosen to protect a player.\nWerewolves have chosen their target.\nSeer has checked a player's identity.\nWitch has made her decision on potion use.\nSYSTEM: Day 1 begins. Players discuss and vote on potential suspects.\nNo candidates decided to run for sheriff. No sheriff in this game anymore.\nNo players deceased during the night.\nAlfonso's speech: Good morning, everyone. I believe that the safety of our village is of utmost importance, and we need a strong guard to protect us from the werewolves. I would like to take on the role of the Guard. My priority is to keep our village safe and to protect the players who are essential to our survival. I understand that we need to be cautious and to work together to identify and eliminate the werewolves. I will do my best to protect the village, and I encourage everyone to stay vigilant and to support each other.\nAmanda's speech: I agree with Alfonso's statement about the importance of having a strong guard to protect our village. His claim to the role of Guard is a positive step towards ensuring our safety. However, we also need to identify and trust the Seer and Witch, as their roles are critical to our survival. Let's work together to protect key players and make informed decisions about who to vote out. By coordinating our efforts, we can increase our chances of eliminating the werewolves and winning the game.\nCharles's speech: Good morning, everyone. I would like to echo Alfonso and Amanda's statements about the importance of having a strong guard and the need to identify and trust the Seer and Witch. Alfonso's claim to the role of Guard seems genuine, and Amanda's statement was supportive and focused on teamwork. I have observed that by working together and supporting each other, we can increase our chances of eliminating the werewolves and winning the game. I will do my best to provide valuable insights and observations without revealing any information that could compromise my identity. Let's stay vigilant and make informed decisions about who to vote out.\nHeather's speech: Good morning, everyone. I agree with Alfonso, Amanda, and Charles that teamwork and caution are crucial for our survival. While Alfonso's claim to the role of Guard is a positive step, we must be careful about trusting anyone too quickly. The werewolves might be trying to manipulate our perceptions, so we need to gather more information before making any decisions. I will do my best to protect the village and support the Seer and Witch, and I encourage everyone to stay vigilant and work together to identify and eliminate the werewolves.\nHeather's speech: Good morning, everyone. I agree with Alfonso, Amanda, and Charles that teamwork and caution are crucial for our survival. While Alfonso's claim to the role of Guard is a positive step, we must be careful about trusting anyone too quickly. The werewolves might be trying to manipulate our perceptions, so we need to gather more information before making any decisions. I will do my best to protect the village and support the Seer and Witch, and I encourage everyone to stay vigilant and work together to identify and eliminate the werewolves.\nKevin's speech: Good morning, everyone. I would like to thank Alfonso for his claim to the role of Guard. His dedication to protecting our village is commendable, and I fully support his statement. It is crucial that we have a strong guard to protect us from the werewolves. However, we must also remember the importance of teamwork and caution. As Heather mentioned, we need to ga