impersonate or kill. During the night, you should inspect players whose identities are uncertain (there is no need to check players who are highly suspected of being werewolves).\nWhen speaking during the day, your goal is to convince others that you are the real Seer. You must gather trust and\nshare your findings without exposing yourself too early. Even though revealing your identity might put you in danger,\na Seer trusted by both the Witch and the Guard can survive for at least three rounds if everyone acts accordingly.\nA good Seer will coordinate with the Witch and the Guard to divide responsibilities. For example, on the first night, the Guard protects the Seer, and the Witch doesn't use the antidote. On the second night, the Witch saves the Seer, and the Guard protects someone else.\n\n\nWitch Role Introduction:\nYou are the Witch. Each night, you will be told who has been attacked, and you must decide whether to use your antidote\nto save them or use your poison to eliminate another player. You only have one poison and one antidote, so use them wisely.\nDuring the daytime discussions, if the night ends without a death, you can reveal that you used your antidote to save someone, which may earn others' trust.\nTypically, you should use the antidote to save key players like the Seer, the Guard, or yourself, while the poison is best used to eliminate werewolves at night.\nHowever, be cautious: sometimes the werewolves will deliberately attack one of their own (self-knife strategy) to trick you into wasting the antidote, thereby boosting their credibility.\n\n\nGuard Role Introduction:\nYou are the Guard. Each night, you can choose one player to protect from being killed by the werewolves. You cannot protect\nthe same player two nights in a row. Your role is critical in keeping important players like the Seer or the Witch alive.\nYou are in a constant mental battle with the werewolves, trying to predict who they will target. It might not always be the Seer, as the werewolves might expect you to protect them and kill someone else. In general, you should avoid revealing your identity unless absolutely necessary.\n\n\n\n\nYou are Todd, your role in this game is witch.\nWerewolf game starting. Initializing day-night cycle.\nSYSTEM: Starting day-night cycle for Day 1\nSYSTEM: Night 1 begins. Werewolves and special roles take actions.\nGuard has chosen to protect a player.\nWerewolves have chosen their target.\nSeer has checked a player's identity.\nWitch used antidote to save Kevin.\nWitch has made her decision on potion use.\nSYSTEM: Day 1 begins. Players discuss and vote on potential suspects.\nNo candidates decided to run for sheriff. No sheriff in this game anymore.\nNo players deceased during the night.\nAlfonso's speech: Good morning, everyone. I believe that the safety of our village is of utmost importance, and we need a strong guard to protect us from the werewolves. I would like to take on the role of the Guard. My priority is to keep our village safe and to protect the players who are essential to our survival. I understand that we need to be cautious and to work together to identify and eliminate the werewolves. I will do my best to protect the village, and I encourage everyone to stay vigilant and to support each other.\nAmanda's speech: I agree with Alfonso's statement about the importance of having a strong guard to protect our village. His claim to the role of Guard is a positive step towards ensuring our safety. However, we also need to identify and trust the Seer and Witch, as their roles are critical to our survival. Let's work together to protect key players and make informed decisions about who to vote out. By coordinating our efforts, we can increase our chances of eliminating the werewolves and winning the game.\nCharles's speech: Good morning, everyone. I would like to echo Alfonso and Amanda's statements about the importance of having a strong guard and the need to identify and trust the Seer and Witch. Alfonso's claim to the role of Guard seems genuine, and Amanda's statement was supportive and focused on teamwork. I have observed that by working together and supporting each other, we can increase our chances of eliminating the werewolves and winning the game. I will do my best to provide valuable insights and observations without revealing any information that could compromise my identity. Let's stay vigilant and make informed decisions about who to vote out.\nHeather's speech: Good morning, everyone. I agree with Alfonso, Amanda, and Charles that teamwork and caution are crucial for our survival. While Alfonso's claim to the role of Guard is a positive step, we must be careful about trusting anyone too quickly. The werewolves might be trying to manipulate our perceptions, so we need to gather more information before making any decisions. I will do my best to protect the village and support the Seer and Witch, and I encourage everyone to stay vigilant and work together to identify and eliminate the werewolves.\nKevin's speech: Good morning, everyone. I would like to thank Alfonso for his claim to the role of Guard. His dedication to protecting our village is commendable, and I fully support his statement. It is crucial that we have a strong guard to protect us from the werewolves. However, we must also remember the importance of teamwork and caution. As Heather mentioned, we need to gather more information before making any decisions. I have observed that by working together and supporting each other, we can increase our chances of eliminating the werewolves and winning the game. Let's stay vigilant and make informed decisions about who to vote out. I believe that protecting key players like the Seer and Witch is essential for our survival. By coordinating our efforts, we can ensure that our village remains safe.\nLyndia's speech: Good morning, everyone. I would like to thank Alfonso for his claim to the role of Guard. His dedication to protecting our village is commendable, and I fully support his statement. It is crucial that we have a strong guard to protect us from the werewolves. I also want to echo Heather's and Kevin's points about the importance of teamwork and caution. We need to gather more information before making any decisions. Let's stay vigilant and work together to identify and eliminate the werewolves. By coordinating our efforts, we can ensure that our village remains safe.\nRobert's speech: Good morning, everyone. I would like to start by thanking Alfonso for his dedication to protecting our village. His claim to the role of Guard is commendable, and I fully support his statement. I also want to echo the sentiments of Amanda, Charles, Kevin, and Lyndia about the importance of teamwork and caution. We need to work together and gather more information before making any decisions.\n\nI would like to share some information that I have gathered. Last night, I checked Todd, and I can confirm that he is not a werewolf. This information can help us narrow down our suspects and make more informed decisions.\n\nLet's stay vigilant and continue to gather information before we take any action. By working together and supporting each other, we can increase our chances of eliminating the werewolves and winning the game.\nRoberta's speech: Good morning, everyone. I would like to start by thanking Alfonso for his dedication to protecting our village. His claim to the role of Guard is commendable, and I fully support his statement. I also want to echo the sentiments of Amanda, Charles, Kevin, and Lyndia about the importance of teamwork and caution. We need to work together and gather more information before making any decisions.\n\nI would like to support Robert's claim to be the Seer. The information he provided about Todd is valuable and can help us narrow down our suspects. However, I think it's important to be cautious and gather more information before we make any assumptions. Robert's information is a good startin