n\nLet's stay vigilant and continue to gather information before we take any action. By working together and supporting each other, we can increase our chances of eliminating the werewolves and winning the game.\nAll players have completed their speeches for today.\nNo player was banished due to a tie.\nBanishment votes:\nRoberta voted for Heather\nRobert voted for Roberta\nTodd voted for Robert\nCharles voted for Roberta\nKevin voted for abstain\nAmanda voted for Heather\nHeather voted for Alfonso\nAlfonso voted for Kevin\nLyndia voted for Alfonso\n(Note: The voting order reflects only the system's query sequence and does not imply any strategic alignment or motive.)\nSYSTEM: Starting day-night cycle for Day 2\nSYSTEM: Night 2 begins. Werewolves and special roles take actions.\nGuard has chosen to protect a player.\nWerewolves have chosen their target.\nSeer has checked a player's identity.\nWitch chose not to use antidote or poison tonight.\nWitch has made her decision on potion use.\nSYSTEM: Day 2 begins. Players discuss and vote on potential suspects.\nPlayers deceased during the night: Amanda\nPlayer Amanda has been eliminated from the game.\nAlfonso's speech: Good morning, everyone. I would like to start by expressing my deepest condolences for Amanda's death. It is a tragic loss for our village, and we must stay vigilant and work together to protect ourselves from the werewolves. Robert's claim to be the Seer is valuable, and I support his statement. The information he provided about Todd is crucial for our survival, and we should trust his judgment. I would like to take on the role of the Guard to protect our village and support the Seer and Witch. By working together and gathering more information, we can increase our chances of eliminating the werewolves and winning the game. Let's stay vigilant and make informed decisions about who to vote out.\nCharles's speech: Good morning, everyone. I would like to start by expressing my deepest condolences for Amanda